Kowloon's Wardens of Iron need current threat data from the Northern Crown approaches before they can adjust seasonal patrol rotations. Three predator types have been reported in densities that exceed safe caravan transit thresholds: mist vipers in the cold valleys, frost-touched wolves along the ridge corridors, and mist-shadow cats near the tree line. Engage one of each and bring back field assessment notes so the wardens can calibrate their next deployment.
Your field reports give Kowloon's patrol command the data they needed to redraw the Northern Crown escort map. The Wardens of Iron have shifted two squads to cover the mist-valley corridors you flagged, and caravan masters are requesting the updated route charts from the Kowloon post office. Seasonal rotation planning can proceed on schedule instead of defaulting to the expensive all-hands deployment.
